wikipedia_page.main: John Edward Nassau Molesworth (1790–1877) was an English cleric of High Church views, vicar of Rochdale for around 38 years.

response: Daniel was the younger son of William Mackinnon, eldest son of the Clan MacKinnon Chief in the western Highlands, and the nephew of General Mackinnon who was killed at the storming of Ciudad Rodrigo. His brother William Alexander was a Member of Parliament,'The Late Colonel Mackinnon', Inverness Courier, 27 July 1836, page 2 whilst his sister Harriet was the wife of the High Church clergyman John Edward Nassau Molesworth.
